<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="45" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">863.00/965a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Acting Minister for Foreign Affairs and
                                    Chancellor of Austria</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schuschnigg</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-26">July 26, 1934</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The sad intelligence of the death of Chancellor Dollfuss at the hand
                                of an assassin shocks and grieves me beyond expression.</p>
                            <p>My fellow citizens join with me in extending to the Government and
                                people of Austria sincerest sympathy in their sorrow.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>